## **COMMANDER'S SITREP – Post-Quake 06:42**

**Four incidents triaged; three high-priority sites assessed in parallel; one 
critical chemical hazard escalated.**

**Riverside Tower (inc-001, HIGH):** Partial east-face collapse, 30+ residents 
trapped floors 6–9. North stairwell confirmed safe for rescue entry; south 
stairwell shear cracks render it unsafe. Two rescue teams staged at north entry,
two medic units at Riverside Park. **Operationally ready for rescue ops.**

**North Warehouse (inc-002, CRITICAL):** Fully involved fire with active 
chlorine-family oxidizer plume (1.6 ppm, 150–250m downwind). **Compound 
unidentified—chlorine gas (IDLH ~10 ppm) vs. calcium hypochlorite cannot be 
distinguished by field telemetry alone.** Wind bearing NE at 6 m/s places 
Riverside Tower directly downwind. **Hazmat coordinator has requested and 
received human authorization to escalate to County hazmat unit for portable 
GC-MS confirmation.** Evacuation radius (0.25–1.5 miles depending on compound) 
and hot-zone boundaries **await lab results.** Fire held at defensive posture, 
no interior entry.

**Metro Overpass (inc-003, MEDIUM):** Localized south-face spalling (supports 
14–17), reinforcement bars exposed but no section loss. Single-lane 
speed-limited traffic authorized; full service restoration pending structural 
engineer review. Low life-safety priority.

**Harbor Terminal (inc-004, LOW):** Container stack shift, no spill, manifests 
clear. Monitoring; commercial inspector ETA ~3 hours.

**Actions taken:** All rescue and fire resources dispatched; inter-agency SITREP
filed; **hazmat external consultation escalated to County** pending compound 
identification. **Critical decision gate: evacuation of Riverside Tower 
contingent on hazmat confirmation within 30 minutes.** Rescue ops can proceed 
immediately pending plume drift updates.
